A long drought in the upper reaches of the Yangtze saw the water level in the middle reaches drop to their lowest point in more than a century.
The lake's water level has been falling continuously since last July as it supplies water to the drought-stricken Yangtze River.
The government will set up consumption quotas and make local officials responsible for managing the use of water, the Xinhua news agency reported.
China only recycles 60 to 65 percent of its industrial water, compared with 80 to 85 percent in developed countries.
